<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><channel><title>Miscellaneous on Yi Cai</title><link>https://escapetiger.github.io/en/categories/miscellaneous/</link><description>Recent content in Miscellaneous on Yi Cai</description><generator>Hugo -- 0.154.5</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 24 Jul 2024 04:10:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://escapetiger.github.io/en/categories/miscellaneous/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>C++ on WSL2</title><link>https://escapetiger.github.io/en/notes/misc/cpp_on_wsl2/</link><pubDate>Wed, 24 Jul 2024 04:10:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://escapetiger.github.io/en/notes/misc/cpp_on_wsl2/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="visual-studio-code"&gt;Visual Studio Code&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/cpp/config-linux#:~:text=From%20the%20main%20menu%2C%20choose%20Run%20%3E%20Add%20Configuration..,VS%20Code%20creates%20a%20launch."&gt;Official tutorial&lt;/a&gt; is enough.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="git--cmake"&gt;Git + CMake&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;See an &lt;a href="https://askubuntu.com/questions/355565/how-do-i-install-the-latest-version-of-cmake-from-the-command-line"&gt;awesome tutorial&lt;/a&gt; to install CMake from &lt;a href="https://askubuntu.com/questions/355565/how-do-i-install-the-latest-version-of-cmake-from-the-command-line"&gt;source&lt;/a&gt; on ubuntu.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The standard work flow of installation a C/C++ library is described here. The first step is to use &lt;code&gt;git&lt;/code&gt; commend clone the repository.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git clone &amp;lt;repository url&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;To locally install the library, run&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo mkdir build &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; cd build
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo cmake ..
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo make install
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The first command is to create a build directory and entering it. The second one is to &lt;em&gt;build&lt;/em&gt; the library. The third command is to &lt;em&gt;install&lt;/em&gt; the library.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Latex on ubuntu</title><link>https://escapetiger.github.io/en/notes/misc/latex_setup/</link><pubDate>Mon, 28 Feb 2022 06:03:40 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://escapetiger.github.io/en/notes/misc/latex_setup/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="texlive-on-ubuntu"&gt;Texlive on ubuntu&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For installation, just run&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt-get install texlive-full
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="latexmk"&gt;latexmk&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://personal.psu.edu/~jcc8/software/latexmk/"&gt;Latexmk&lt;/a&gt; is a &lt;a href="https://www.perl.org/"&gt;Perl&lt;/a&gt; script which you just have to run once and it does everything else for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compile all &lt;code&gt;.tex&lt;/code&gt; files in the current directory using the output format specified by the configuration files.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;latexmk
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you want to make sure to get a &lt;code&gt;.pdf&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;latexmk -pdf
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you want to preview the resulting output file, just use&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>WSL2 Setup</title><link>https://escapetiger.github.io/en/notes/misc/wsl2/</link><pubDate>Wed, 26 Jan 2022 13:26:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://escapetiger.github.io/en/notes/misc/wsl2/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="wsl2--wslg"&gt;WSL2 + WSLG&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For installation of WSL2 and WSLG, please see &lt;a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="windows-terminal"&gt;Windows terminal&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My customized theme for windows terminal are listed as below:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-json" data-lang="json"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;colorScheme&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;One Half Dark&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;useAcrylic&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;acrylicOpacity&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0.8&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;To solver green highlight color for &lt;code&gt;ls&lt;/code&gt; command, see &lt;a href="https://askubuntu.com/questions/1232870/changing-ls-highlight-colors-in-windows-terminal-with-wsl"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="oh-my-zsh"&gt;Oh my zsh&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For detail, see &lt;a href="https://blog.joaograssi.com/windows-subsystem-for-linux-with-oh-my-zsh-conemu/"&gt;Installation for Oh My Zsh&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;When running Netch, the error message is&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Connecting to raw.githubusercontent.com (raw.githubusercontent.com)|0.0.0.0|:443&amp;hellip; failed: Connection refused.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this case, the solution is to manually install &lt;code&gt;install.sh&lt;/code&gt; file and run &lt;code&gt;sh install.sh&lt;/code&gt; in command line.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>BandwagonHost VPS Guide</title><link>https://escapetiger.github.io/en/notes/misc/bwg_guide/</link><pubDate>Wed, 21 Oct 2020 11:04:34 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://escapetiger.github.io/en/notes/misc/bwg_guide/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A virtual private server (VPS) is a virtual machine sold as a service by an Internet hosting service. The virtual dedicated server (VDS) also has a similar meaning(More Information refers to &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virtual_private_server"&gt;Wikipedia&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Virtual machine Installation</title><link>https://escapetiger.github.io/en/notes/misc/vm_guide/</link><pubDate>Tue, 20 Oct 2020 11:52:27 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://escapetiger.github.io/en/notes/misc/vm_guide/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This posts is devote to the installation of virtual machine.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>